<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 25 at 4:08PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of
Caswell County through 445 PM EDT...
At 408 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Providence, moving southeast at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Yanceyville...
Bethel...
Providence...
Prospect Hill...
Gatewood...
Leasburg...
and Hamer.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
